          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r1')">12,000 km</button>
        </div>
        <div class="quiz-reveal" id="r1"><strong>8,891 km</strong> ‚Äî the longest undefended international border in the world. And yet, despite this closeness, the two countries are culturally more different than most people expect.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-card" style="animation-delay:0.1s">
        <p class="quiz-q">üåç Q2. What percentage of Toronto's population was born outside Canada?</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r2')">~25%</button>
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r2')">~35%</button>
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, true, 'r2')">~50%</button>
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r2')">~65%</button>
        </div>
        <div class="quiz-reveal" id="r2"><strong>Around 50%</strong> of Toronto residents were born outside Canada ‚Äî making it one of the most immigrant-majority cities on Earth. For context, NYC's figure is around 37%. Toronto is on another level entirely.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-card" style="animation-delay:0.2s">
        <p class="quiz-q">üí¨ Q3. Which phrase is most stereotypically Canadian?</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r3')">"Let's get this done!"</button>
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, true, 'r3')">"Sorry, eh?"</button>
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r3')">"You're welcome, sir."</button>
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r3')">"No problem at all, buddy."</button>
        </div>
        <div class="quiz-reveal" id="r3"><strong>"Sorry, eh?"</strong> ‚Äî Canadians famously apologize even when they're not at fault, and the filler word "eh" is genuinely embedded in everyday Canadian speech. These aren't just jokes ‚Äî they reflect deeper cultural values of politeness, deference, and community harmony.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="quiz-card" style="animation-delay:0.3s">
        <p class="quiz-q">üèôÔ∏è Q4. Toronto is sometimes called "New York City's little brother." How does its population compare to NYC?</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r4')">About the same size</button>
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r4')">Half the size</button>
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, true, 'r4')">About one-third the size</button>
          <button class="quiz-opt" onclick="answer(this, false, 'r4')">About one-fifth the size</button>
        </div>
        <div class="quiz-reveal" id="r4">NYC has <strong>~8.2 million</strong> residents; Toronto has <strong>~2.9 million</strong> ‚Äî roughly one-third. Yet Toronto punches far above its weight in diversity, culture, and innovation. Size isn't everything.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="fun-fact">
        <div class="ff-icon">üí°</div>
        <p><strong>Discussion starter for the group:</strong> Before we go deeper ‚Äî what's your gut feeling about Canada vs the USA? Do you expect them to be more similar or more different? Vote with your hands and keep that intuition in mind as we go.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
