      <!-- Accordion: neighbourhood spotlights -->
      <h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif; font-size:22px; margin: 32px 0 16px;">Toronto Neighbourhood Spotlights</h3>
      <p style="color:var(--warm-gray); font-size:14px; margin-bottom:20px;">Toronto is really a city of neighbourhoods ‚Äî each one a distinct cultural world. Click to explore.</p>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
          <span>üåø Kensington Market ‚Äî The Bohemian Heart</span>
          <span class="accordion-arrow">‚ñº</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-body">A historic, eclectic neighbourhood that has been home to waves of immigrants ‚Äî Jewish, Portuguese, Caribbean, Chinese, and more. Today it's Toronto's most bohemian spot: vintage shops, global street food, murals, and an almost defiant resistance to gentrification. It embodies Toronto's mosaic identity in a single square kilometre. Compare this to NYC's Williamsburg ‚Äî similar creative energy, but significantly more gentrified and expensive.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
          <span>üè≠ The Distillery District ‚Äî Industrial Chic</span>
          <span class="accordion-arrow">‚ñº</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-body">A 13-acre preserved Victorian industrial complex turned cultural hub ‚Äî galleries, boutiques, restaurants, and studios in stunning heritage brick buildings. Toronto has managed what many cities dream of: authentic adaptive reuse that serves culture rather than just luxury condos. The Christmas Market here is legendary.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
          <span>üåä Waterfront & The Islands</span>
          <span class="accordion-arrow">‚ñº</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-body">Toronto sits on Lake Ontario ‚Äî one of the Great Lakes ‚Äî and its waterfront is a genuine asset. The Toronto Islands (a short ferry ride away) offer a car-free escape with beaches, kayaking, and skyline views. This is something NYC's Manhattan simply can't match. Torontonians love the idea of being able to swim in a lake within sight of the city's skyscrapers.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item">
        <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
          <span>üçú Scarborough ‚Äî The World in One Borough</span>
          <span class="accordion-arrow">‚ñº</span>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-body">Often overlooked by tourists, Scarborough is where Toronto's true multicultural density lives ‚Äî Sri Lankan, South Asian, East African, Caribbean, Chinese communities all thriving side by side. The food here ‚Äî Tamil, Hakka-Chinese fusion, roti ‚Äî is some of the best and most authentic in North America. No equivalent neighbourhood exists in NYC at the same scale and density.</div>
      </div>

